name: BushWhack Boogie
description:
Introduction

High Clearance 4X4 vehicle required to get to the trailhead.

Approach

There are two approach options. One from the South East side of the river and the other from the North West side of the river. Both options require the same sandstone climb-up exiting or approaching.

Descent

Several deep potholes in this canyon that could be keepers although there are easy walk arounds.

Exit

Good navigation skills to find the exit/entrance climb-up. The exit/entrance climb-up require some 5.6 moves up to the sandstone ramp. The sandstone exit/entrance ramp is narrow and exposed in places and would not be recommended when wet.
